  <h1>Samsung Galaxy S26 Ultra <span class="accent">EMI in Bangladesh.</span></h1>
  <p class="lede">Pay monthly instead of upfront. 0% interest plans from 8 BD banks across 3, 6, and 12 months. Complete breakdown with monthly amounts and eligibility.</p>
  <div class="last-updated">Last updated: <time datetime="2026-04-27">April 27, 2026</time></div>
</header>

<main class="content">

<h2>EMI at a glance</h2>
<p>Almost every authorized S26 Ultra retailer in Bangladesh supports 0% EMI with eligible credit cards. You pay zero interest — the bank and retailer split a processing fee behind the scenes. Your monthly payment is simply the phone price divided by the number of months.</p>

<h2>Monthly payment breakdown — every variant</h2>
<table class="data-table">
<thead><tr><th>Variant &amp; Price</th><th>3 Months</th><th>6 Months</th><th>12 Months</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td><strong>256GB UAE</strong><br>৳1,55,000</td><td>৳51,666/mo</td><td>৳25,833/mo</td><td>৳12,916/mo</td></tr>
<tr class="hl"><td><strong>256GB Official</strong><br>৳1,89,999</td><td>৳63,333/mo</td><td>৳31,666/mo</td><td>৳15,833/mo</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>512GB UAE</strong><br>৳1,72,000</td><td>৳57,333/mo</td><td>৳28,666/mo</td><td>৳14,333/mo</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>512GB Official</strong><br>৳2,09,999</td><td>৳69,999/mo</td><td>৳35,000/mo</td><td>৳17,500/mo</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>1TB UAE</strong><br>৳2,05,000</td><td>৳68,333/mo</td><td>৳34,166/mo</td><td>৳17,083/mo</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>1TB Official</strong><br>৳2,49,999</td><td>৳83,333/mo</td><td>৳41,666/mo</td><td>৳20,833/mo</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h2>Banks that offer 0% EMI on S26 Ultra</h2>
<p>All 8 of these banks participate in 0% EMI programs with major S26 Ultra retailers in Bangladesh:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Eastern Bank Limited (EBL)</strong> — widest retailer network, accepted at every major store</li>
<li><strong>City Bank</strong> — American Express + Visa + Mastercard all eligible</li>
<li><strong>BRAC Bank</strong> — Tara card holders get extra cashback events</li>
<li><strong>Standard Chartered</strong> — often runs festival bonus EMI months (Eid, Pohela Boishakh)</li>
<li><strong>Dutch-Bangla Bank</strong> — widest consumer reach in BD</li>
<li><strong>Prime Bank</strong> — competitive rates on 12-month plans</li>
<li><strong>Mutual Trust Bank (MTB)</strong> — accepted at Dazzle, Sumash Tech, Star Tech</li>
<li><strong>Commercial Bank of Ceylon</strong> — premium card EMI with extra benefits</li>
</ul>

<h2>Eligibility — what you need</h2>
<ul>
<li>A valid credit card from one of the listed banks (debit cards don't qualify)</li>
<li>Available credit limit covering the full phone price</li>
<li>Minimum card age (varies by bank, typically 6 months)</li>
<li>No missed EMI payments on other purchases in the last 12 months</li>
<li>Card needs to be active and not near its renewal date</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to apply — at the store</h2>
<ol>
<li>Pick your S26 Ultra variant and confirm price with the retailer</li>
<li>Tell the cashier you want EMI and specify 3/6/12 months</li>
<li>Hand over your eligible credit card</li>
<li>Sign the EMI agreement form (the retailer prints it)</li>
<li>Phone is yours same day — monthly deduction starts next billing cycle</li>
</ol>

<h2>Hidden costs to watch for</h2>
<div class="callout">
<div class="title">▸ Warning</div>
<p>Not every retailer offers true 0% EMI. Some inflate the cash price by 3-5% when you choose EMI. Always compare:</p>
<ol>
<li>Cash price (card or bKash)</li>
<li>EMI price for the same variant</li>
</ol>
<p>If the EMI price is higher, it's not real 0% EMI — it's hidden interest. Sumash Tech, Star Tech, Dazzle, and the official Samsung stores offer genuine 0% EMI at their listed prices.</p>
</div>

<h2>Which EMI duration is smartest?</h2>
<p><strong>3 months:</strong> Best if you can afford ৳50-80k/month. Minimizes credit card exposure, fastest to pay off.</p>
<p><strong>6 months:</strong> The sweet spot for most BD buyers. Monthly payment is comfortable (~৳30k), still finished before next Eid.</p>
<p><strong>12 months:</strong> Lowest monthly burden (~৳15-20k) but ties up your credit limit for a full year. Only choose this if your monthly cash flow is tight.</p>

<h2>Common mistakes to avoid</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Not checking your credit limit first</strong> — bank will decline at POS if insufficient</li>
<li><strong>Choosing 12 months when 6 months fits</strong> — ties up credit longer than needed</li>
<li><strong>Using a card that renews mid-EMI</strong> — can cause billing complications</li>
<li><strong>Confusing "EMI" with "installment"</strong> — some retailers offer interest-bearing installments disguised as EMI</li>
</ul>




